88769.「……なんですって！？\n 依頼品の <%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>が\n 足:
What's wrong? You are missing <%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>
of the requested items? And 9 of them, too.

88770.「待ってください。\n 今すぐ 帳簿を 確かめます！: Wait a minute. I'll check the books right now!

88771.「……おかしいわ。\n 帳簿には １個だと書いてあるのに。\n でも 依頼主さん:
That's strange. The ledger says there was only
one. But the client would never lie.

88773.「それ……俺です。\n 書き間違えちまって あとで 直すつもりが\n うっかり:
That's me. I made a mistake and meant to fix
it later, but I accidentally forgot.

88774.「この アホッ！ ボケッ！ スカタン！！\n てめえ なんてヘマを しやがったん:
You asshole! Pratfall! Scatan! What a screw-up
you've made! You've ruined the Woodworking
Guild's credibility, haven't you?

88775.「ソコまで言うこた ねーだろうがっ！\n ちょっとした 間違いぐれえ\n 誰だっ:
You don't have to go that far! Everyone makes
a little mistake!

88777.「身内でモメる前に 客に どう落とし前を\n つけるか考えるのが 先だろうがッ！:
Before you get into a quarrel within yourselves, you should think about how to settle up with your customers first! You Usura
idiots! You should be ashamed of yourselves!

88778.「すまねえ カンナお嬢さん……。\n つい 頭に血がのぼっちまって……。:
I'm sorry, Miss Kanna. I just got a little too
much blood in my head.

88779.「なぁに わかりゃあ いいんだよ。\n ……門弟のしでかしたヘマは\n アタシが:
You know what? It's all right. I'll take care
of what the disciples did wrong. Leave it to
me.

88781.マスター・カンナは またたく間に\n<%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>を ９個 作:
Guildmaster Kanna quickly built up nine
<%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>s!

88782.「……これでいい。\n 迷惑をかけちまった わびもかねて\n あとで アタシが:
That's fine. I'll deliver it later as an
apology for the trouble I caused you.

88783.「カンナお嬢さん……。\n ありがとうございやすっ！: Miss Kanna. Thank you very much!

88784.「なぁに いいってコトよ。\n ただし！ 二度と 同じヘマは\n するんじゃない:
What do you mean? It's fine. However! Don't
ever make the same mistake again.

88785.「へぇ……。ピーピー泣きごと言って\n 職人達に 迷惑かけてんだろうと思ったら\:
Wow. I thought he was probably whining and
causing trouble for the craftspeople, but he
seems to be doing a pretty good job.

88786.「なんだぁ てめえ！\n 俺達のマスターに向かって\n 失礼なクチを ききやがっ:
What the hell, you! You dare to be so rude to
our master!

88787.「……待ってください 皆さん。\n その人は……。: Wait a minute, ladies and gentlemen. The man.

88789.「ご紹介します 皆さん。\n 私の母 カナノコです。\n お母さん。こちらは 職:
Let me introduce to you, ladies and gentlemen.
This is my mother Kananok. My mother. These
are our craftsmen.

88790.「ふん。木工職人なんかに興味はないよ。\n それより どうして アタシが来たのか:
I'm not interested in woodworkers. But you
know why I'm here, don't you? Kanna.

88791.「好きにさせるのは ２０歳になるまで。\n 成人したら 家に帰って\n ムコをと:
I will not let you do what you want until you are 20 years old. When you come of age, you will go home and take a husband.
That's the deal.

88793.「実家に帰るだって！？\n お おい 待ってくれよ！\n この木工ギルドは どう:
You're going back to your parents' house? Hey,
wait a minute! What's going to happen to this
Woodworking Guild?

88794.「あたしの 知ったこっちゃないね。\n さあ 来るんだよ！ カンナ！！:
It's none of my business. Come on, come on!
Kanna!

88796.「言いたいことがあるなら はっきり言いな。: If you have something to say, say it clearly.

88797.「ご ごめんなさい！\n ……お母さん お願いします。\n 私の後継者を決めるま:
I'm sorry! Mother, please. Please give me time
to decide who will succeed me.

88798.「ちゃんと 約束は守ります。\n でも……次のギルドマスターが決まらないうちに\:
I will keep my promise. But if I quit before
the next guildmaster is decided, it will cause
trouble to many people.

88799.「……ふん。しかたないね。\n ただし 長くは待たないよ。\n さっさと 次のギ:
Hmm. I'll have to do it. But I won't wait
long. Quickly decide on the next guildmaster.

88802.「もっと 皆さんと一緒に\n 木工職人道を 追求したかったけれど\n ……もう:
I would have loved to pursue the Woodworker
path with you all more, but it looks like time
is running out.

88803.「次のギルドマスターには\n 私なんかより ずっと しっかりした\n すごウデの:
I'm sure that the next guildmaster will be a
much more solid and skilled craftsman than I
am.

88804.「<pc>さん。すばらしい\n <%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>を 作っていただ:
<pc>. Thank you for creating this
wonderful <%sEV_SYOK_ITEM>.

88805.「こちらは ささやかながら 今回のお礼です。\n 本当に お疲れ様でした。:
This is just a small token of our
appreciation. Thank you very much for your
hard work.

88806.「これで 職人レベル４６以上に 成長できます。\n 次の限界は レベル５０になる:
Now you can grow to artisan level 46 or above.
Your next limit will be when you reach level
50. Until then, please keep up the good work!

115038.「私の家の事情で お騒がせしてしまって\n ごめんなさい みなさん。\n ……さ:
I'm sorry to have disturbed you with my home
situation, ladies and gentlemen. Now I have to
get back to work.
